lass, and the social status of the artist in early modern Bologna; approaches to exhibiting artworks in noble Bolognese collections; the reputations of local women artists; the popularity of Bolognese quadratura painting; and the relative success of both contemporary and earlier Bolognese artists with Italian collectors.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 4aArt and Material Culture. 4aCultural Studies. 4aEarly Modern Period. 4aHistory. 7aART / History / Baroque & Rococo.2bisacsh  aAlbicini.  aBologna.  aGonzaga.  aMedici.  aSeventeenth-century art.  aSirani.1 aBohn, Babette, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBohn, Babette, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFumagalli, Elena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGhelfi, Barbara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMorselli, , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMorselli, Raffaella, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPiccinelli, Roberta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVries, Joyce de, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311066152108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2019z9783110605785oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2019 Englishz978311061001708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048537556zCo-access DOI >